<%- include('partials/header', { title: 'Privacy Policy - Lineside' }) %>

<body style="background-color: #f8fafc; font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; color: #0f172a; margin: 0; padding: 0; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;">
    <main style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; min-height: 100vh; display: flex; flex-direction: column;">

        <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
            <a href="/" style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: #1e3a8a; text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; transition: opacity 0.2s;" onmouseover="this.style.opacity='0.8'" onmouseout="this.style.opacity='1'">
                <div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 50%; background: #1e3a8a;"></div>
                Lineside
            </a>
        </div>

        <div style="padding: 2.5rem; background: #ffffff; border-radius: 16px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05), 0 2px 4px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; flex: 1;">

            <h1 style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #0f172a; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p style="color: #64748b; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 0.95rem;"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> June 2026</p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #64748b;">Welcome to Lineside. This Privacy Policy explains how your personal data is collected, used, stored, and protected when you use the Lineside web application. For the purposes of the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR), the Data Controller is Harry Faulkner, United Kingdom.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #64748b;">To provide the core functionality of logging and mapping your spots, we collect the following types of information:</p>

            <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #64748b; padding-left: 0.5rem;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Account Information:</strong> When you sign up, we collect your first name, last name, username, email address, and a securely hashed password. If you use Google to sign in, we receive your email and basic profile information. Authentication services provided by Google are subject to Google's privacy policies.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">User-Generated Content:</strong> When you log a spot, we collect the title, description, and timestamp. If you upload photos, the image files and their embedded technical EXIF data (e.g., shutter speed, ISO, focal length, camera model) are stored.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Location Data:</strong> If you grant permission, we collect and store the precise latitude and longitude of your spots to map them.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Essential Cookies:</strong> We use secure, <code>httpOnly</code> cookies (<code>access_token</code> and <code>refresh_token</code>) strictly to keep you securely logged in. Lineside itself does not use advertising or analytics cookies. However, third-party authentication via Google may involve Google-set cookies which are subject to their own policies.</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="height: 1px; background: #e2e8f0; margin: 2rem 0;"></div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">2. How We Use Your Information & Lawful Basis</h2>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #64748b;">Under the UK GDPR, we must have a "lawful basis" for processing your data. We use your information for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #64748b; padding-left: 0.5rem;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">To Provide the Service (Contractual Necessity):</strong> Creating your account, managing your session, rendering your personal spot history, and providing spot-sharing features.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">To Improve Lineside (Legitimate Interests):</strong> Aggregating non-identifiable hotspot data for the global map view to benefit the community.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Location Features (Consent):</strong> We only access your device's live geolocation if you explicitly grant us permission via your browser or device.</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="height: 1px; background: #e2e8f0; margin: 2rem 0;"></div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">3. Data Storage, Security, and Retention</h2>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #64748b; padding-left: 0.5rem;">
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Data Processors:</strong> We use third-party service providers who process personal data on our behalf under appropriate data processing agreements. These are described below.</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Security Measures:</strong> We use industry-standard security measures including encrypted connections (HTTPS/TLS), secure access controls, and secure password hashing to protect your personal data.</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Data Retention:</strong> We retain your personal data and spot history for as long as your account remains active. If you delete a specific spot or your entire account, the associated data and image files are deleted from active systems and removed from our backups within 30 days in accordance with our backup retention schedule.</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">International Transfers:</strong> Lineside uses global infrastructure providers. Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries outside the UK/EEA (such as the United States). In such cases, we rely on standard contractual clauses or other legally approved safeguards to ensure your data remains protected.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">Third-Party Services We Use</h3>

                        <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #64748b;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Supabase</strong> — Database storage and user authentication. Stores your account information and spot data on servers within the European Union.</p>

                        <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #64748b;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Cloudflare R2</strong> — Photo storage. Photos you upload are stored using Cloudflare's object storage service.</p>

                        <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #64748b;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Resend</strong> — Transactional email delivery. When you register or request a password reset, your email address is passed to Resend solely to deliver that email. Resend does not use your data for marketing.</p>

                        <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #64748b;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Sentry</strong> — Application error monitoring. When an error occurs, Sentry may automatically collect technical information such as the error message, stack trace, browser type, and operating system. Sentry does <em>not</em> collect your name, email address, or any content you have submitted to Lineside. A random 10% sample of page-load events is also captured for performance monitoring. Data is retained for 90 days.</p>

                        <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; color: #64748b;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Sightengine</strong> — Automated image moderation. Photos you upload may be automatically scanned to detect content that violates our community guidelines (such as nudity or graphic violence). The image is transmitted to Sightengine for analysis and is not stored by Sightengine beyond the duration of that request. Sightengine does not link the image to your identity.

            <div style="height: 1px; background: #e2e8f0; margin: 2rem 0;"></div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">4. Data Sharing and Visibility</h2>
            <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #64748b; padding-left: 0.5rem;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Public Map:</strong> General spot locations and recent unit numbers are aggregated to highlight spotting "hotspots" to other users. Hotspot information is aggregated and designed not to identify individual users.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Shared Links:</strong> If you use the spot sharing feature, anyone with the unique generated link can view the specific details and image of that spot. These links are not publicly indexed but should be treated as public by anyone who possesses the link.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">We do not sell your personal data to advertisers or data brokers.</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="height: 1px; background: #e2e8f0; margin: 2rem 0;"></div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">5. Your Rights</h2>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #64748b;">Under data protection laws, you have rights including:</p>
            <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #64748b; padding-left: 0.5rem;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Right of Access & Portability:</strong> You can request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Right to Rectification:</strong> You can edit your profile information at any time within the app settings.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Right to Erasure (Right to be Forgotten):</strong> You can permanently delete individual spots or your entire account at any time. Data will be removed from active systems promptly and from backups according to our backup retention schedules.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Right to Restrict Processing:</strong> You have the right to ask us to restrict the processing of your personal data in certain circumstances.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Right to Object:</strong> You have the right to object to processing of your personal data where we are relying on a legitimate interest.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Right to Withdraw Consent:</strong> You can revoke Lineside's access to your device's live geolocation at any time via your browser or device permissions.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">Right to Lodge a Complaint:</strong> You have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO).</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="height: 1px; background: #e2e8f0; margin: 2rem 0;"></div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">6. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; color: #64748b;">Lineside is not intended for children under 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 16. If we become aware that we have collected personal data from a child under this age, we will take steps to securely delete that information.</p>

            <div style="height: 1px; background: #e2e8f0; margin: 2rem 0;"></div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">7. Updates to this Policy</h2>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; color: #64748b;">We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated through the application or website. The latest version will always be available on this page.</p>

            <div style="height: 1px; background: #e2e8f0; margin: 2rem 0;"></div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #0f172a; font-weight: 700;">8. Contact & Reporting</h2>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #64748b;">If you have any questions regarding your data, or if you need to report inappropriate or copyrighted material shared via a public Lineside link, please contact us:</p>
            <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #64748b;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;"><strong>Data Controller:</strong> Harry Faulkner, United Kingdom</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hfaulkner2006@gmail.com" style="color: #1e3a8a; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500;">hfaulkner2006@gmail.com</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #64748b;">If you are based in the UK and feel that your data has not been handled correctly, you can find details on how to contact the ICO at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: #1e3a8a; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500;">ico.org.uk</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #94a3b8; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500;">
            &copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> Lineside
        </div>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
